@page "/components/HxOffcanvas"

<h1>@nameof(HxOffcanvas)</h1>

<p class="lead">
	<a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.0/components/offcanvas/">Bootstrap Offcanvas</a> component (aka Drawer).
</p>

@*<ComponentApiDoc Type="typeof(HxOffcanvas)" />
* Header
* Parameters
* Event callbacks
* Methods*@

<h3>Parameters</h3>
<ul>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.HeaderText), @nameof(HxOffcanvas.HeaderTemplate)</strong><br />
		Header.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.BodyTemplate)</strong><br />
		Body.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.FooterTemplate)</strong><br />
		Footer.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.CloseOnEscape)</strong><br />
		Indicates whether the offcanvas closes when escape key is pressed. Default value is true.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.Size)</strong><br />
		Size of the offcanvas. Default is <code>@nameof(OffcanvasSize).@nameof(OffcanvasSize.Regular)</code>.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.BackdropEnabled)</strong><br />
		Indicates whether the offcanvas uses a backdrop. Default value is true.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.ScrollingEnabled)</strong><br />
		Indicates whether body (page) scrolling is allowed while offcanvas is open. Default is <code>false</code>.
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.CssClass)</strong><br />
		Offcanvas CSS class. Added to root div (.modal).
	</li>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.OnClosed)</strong><br />
		Raised when offcanvas is closed (whatever reason it is).
	</li>
</ul>

<h3>Event callbacks</h3>
<ul>
	<li>
		<strong>OnClosed</strong><br />
		Raised when offcanvas is closed (whatever reason it is).
	</li>
</ul>

<h3>Methods</h3>
<ul>
	<li>
		<strong>@nameof(HxOffcanvas.ShowAsync), @nameof(HxOffcanvas.HideAsync)</strong><br />
		Shows / hides offcanvas. <code>Show</code> is allowed to be called although the offcanvas is already open (does nothing).
	</li>
</ul>

<div class="alert alert-warning" role="alert">
	Similar to modals, only one offcanvas can be shown at a time.<br/>
	(We hide the current offcanvas if you open a new one.)
</div>

